The paper proposes a novel CNN architecture for view synthesis, which involves rectification, dense correspondences, and blending masks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of an encoder-decoder network and the mention of high computational complexity suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
